{% extends 'layout.html.twig' %}

{% block content %}
<div class="card">
    <h1>Welcome to Phoenix Framework</h1>
    <p>
        Congratulations! Your Phoenix Framework application is up and running.
        This starter template demonstrates the key patterns and conventions of the framework.
    </p>

    <nav class="nav">
        <a href="/welcome" class="btn">Try the Demo</a>
    </nav>

    <h2>What's Included</h2>
    <p>This starter project demonstrates:</p>
    <ul style="margin-left: 20px; margin-bottom: 20px;">
        <li><strong>CQRS Pattern</strong> - UseCases with Input, Handler, and Result</li>
        <li><strong>Service Providers</strong> - Module registration and DI configuration</li>
        <li><strong>Configuration</strong> - Schema-validated configuration system</li>
        <li><strong>Routing</strong> - League Route integration</li>
        <li><strong>View Layer</strong> - Twig templating</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Project Structure</h2>
    <pre><code>src/App/
├── ApplicationKernel.php        # Application entry point
├── Http/
│   ├── RouteProvider.php        # Route definitions
│   └── Controller/              # HTTP controllers
└── Modules/
    └── Welcome/
        ├── WelcomeServiceProvider.php
        ├── WelcomeConfigSchemaProvider.php
        └── UseCases/
            ├── CreateGreeting/  # Full UseCase example
            │   ├── CreateGreetingInput.php
            │   ├── CreateGreetingUseCase.php
            │   ├── CreateGreetingHandler.php
            │   └── CreateGreetingResult.php
            └── GetGreeting/     # Simpler UseCase example</code></pre>

    <h2>Next Steps</h2>
    <ol style="margin-left: 20px;">
        <li>Explore the <code>src/App/Modules/Welcome</code> module</li>
        <li>Create your own module following the same pattern</li>
        <li>Read the <a href="https://github.com/fastbill/phoenix-framework/tree/main/docs">Phoenix documentation</a></li>
    </ol>
</div>
{% endblock %}
